tomo
Homonym Number:  1
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a cave or hole;  a chute-like hole made by water in especially volcanic material. [Maori ?]; a water-worn hole; a sink-hole in limestone country f. ?Maori <i>tomoau</i>, abyss (Williams 435), or the noun f.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
